## Separator Component

The `Separator` component is a presentational UI element used to visually separate content. It's built upon the `SeparatorPrimitive.Root` from `@radix-ui/react-separator` and leverages the `cn` utility for class name merging.

### Purpose

This component provides a simple and customizable horizontal or vertical line to divide distinct sections of your user interface.

### Key Exports

*   **`Separator`**: The main React component for rendering a separator.

### Props

This component accepts all the standard props from `@radix-ui/react-separator`, along with the following:

*   **`className`** (string, optional): Allows for custom styling of the separator element.
*   **`orientation`** (enum: `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default: `'horizontal'`): Determines the orientation of the separator.
*   **`decorative`** (boolean, default: `true`): Indicates whether the separator is purely decorative and should be ignored by assistive technologies.

### Usage Example

```tsx
import { Separator } from '@/components/ui/separator';

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Section 1</p>
      <Separator /> {/* Horizontal separator */}
      <p>Section 2</p>

      <div style={{ display: 'flex', height: '100px' }}>
        <span>Item A</span>
        <Separator orientation="vertical" /> {/* Vertical separator */}
        <span>Item B</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default MyComponent;
```
